HEADWORD: Incogitative
<hw>In*cog"i*ta*tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Not
cogitative; not thinking; lacking the power of thought; <as>as, a
vegetable is an <ex>incogitative</ex> being</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Locke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

